\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:21:21'),(277,'#tool #kali #pentest #maltego #methodology','Maltego can comb popular social media, public records, and job recruiting websites to fingerprint an individual based on limited information\n  A researcher could gather information such as everywhere an individual has lived,\n	one business, people with which they socialize, special interests, favorite sport\nteams, and other useful data for future research and social engineering attack',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:23:41'),(278,'#beef #tool #kali #intro #pentest','\nBeEF is a browser-based exploit package that \"hooks\" one or more\n	browsers as beachheads for launching attacks. A user can be hooked by accessing a\n	customized URL and continue to see typical web traffic, while an attacker has access\n	to the user\'s session.\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:51:37'),(279,'#beef #tool #kali #intro #pentest','ifk: beef is useful while pentester has access to the user_s session',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:52:06'),(280,'#beef #tool #kali #intro #pentest','BeEF bypasses network security appliances and host–based, anti-virus applications by targeting the vulnerabilities found in common browsers, such as ff and ie',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 12:53:56'),(281,'#kali #tool #beef #run#server #tuto','\ncd /usr/share/beef-xss\n./beef\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 13:28:54'),(282,'#kali #tool #beef #methodology','\nu need to redirect the victim into ur beef_url_hook(in_running_server: http://127.0.0.1:3000/hook.js) \n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 13:07:08'),(283,'#kali #tool #panel #admin#beef #run #tuto','\nafter running the server of beef, \nu need to go in interface_ui|web_admin of beef:\n	go at: http://127.0.0.1:3000/ui/panel\n		which u see in the terminal of running of beef_server\n	\n	in the first time of connection to server_beef:\n		username: beef\n		password: beef\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 13:21:51'),(284,'#burp #kali #methodology #tool','\nBurp Proxy is a tool that intercepts HTTP and HTTPS traffic. It allows a Penetration\nTester to examine an application, its vulnerabilities, and the two-way traffic between\na client and a web server. Burp Proxy is very popular because of its ability to not\nonly examine the traffic, but also, it manipulates requests\n\nWhen a user enters a URL in their web browser such as http://www.DrChaos.com, \nthey expect to be directed to the website. A proxy server will\nintercept that request and send it on behalf of a client\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 14:04:42'),(285,'#mysql #change #column#order',NULL,NULL,'ALTER TABLE table00 CHANGE COLUMN col00 col00 VARCHAR(50) AFTER col01;\n  then col00 will be placed after col01\n  note thate there is no before col00\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 15:16:19'),(286,'potatoes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 15:30:55'),(287,'does_it work?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 15:40:21'),(288,'#mysql #had#issue #tuto','\ni removed a column which is a key\ni set it back but the place of that new_col is in the bottom\n\nsolution:\n=====================================\ni removed totally col00\ni recreate it but no auto_increment and not a key\ni set its place in the head of all col by:\n  ALTER TABLE Employees CHANGE COLUMN col00 col00 VARCHAR(50) AFTER first_col;\n  	there is no: before first_col;\n  ALTER TABLE table00 CHANGE COLUMN first_col first_col VARCHAR(50) AFTER col00;\n  	now col00 is the first of all columns\nadd the fact that col00 is an auto_increment and a primary key by:\n  alter table table00 change col00 col00 int(5) auto_increment key;\n\nand it\'s done\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-01-14 15:40:48'),(289,'#tool#kali #msfvenom #intro','msfvenom is a combination of Msfpayload and Msfencode, putting both of these tools into a single framework instance. The advantages of msfvenom are:\n    One single tool\n	    Standardized command line options