            \n\n          |                       |\n          +------+----------------+\n                 +-- branch_master\n\nmerge will bring the modification in branch00 to the branch_master\n	bcz the work in branch00 is ok and ready to be added in branch_master\n	to do that:\n		u_re in branch00\n		go to branch_master [plz do not forget this]\n		do the merge\n			git merge branch00\n\nnow we have this one:\n   \n                       +--------+     +--------+       +--------+            +--------+ \n               +------>|        +---->|        +------>|        +----->>+--->|        +-> \n               |       +--------+     +--------+       +--------+       ^    +--------+ \n               |                                                        |\n          +----+---+     +--------+                                     |\n          |        +---->|        +-------------------------------------+\n          +--------+     +--------+              \n\n          |                       |\n          +------+----------------+\n                 +-- branch_master\n\n\nlike this exactly:\n        \n                                 +- branch00\n                       +---------+------------------------------+\n                       |                                        |\n\n                       +--------+     +--------+       +--------+            +--------+ \n               +------>|        +---->|        +------>|        +       +--->|        +-> \n               |       +--------+     +--------+       +--------+       ^    +--------+ \n               |                                                        |\n          +----+---+     +--------+                                     |\n          |        +---->|        +-------------------------------------+\n          +--------+     +--------+              \n\n          |                       |\n          +------+----------------+\n                 +-- branch_master\n\nwe can see that we can delete branch00 by\n    git branch -d branch00\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 16:15:58'),(493,'#git -branch -intro',NULL,NULL,'\nafter creating a branch with:\n	git branch branch00\nu did some commits in branch00\nu went back in branch_master\nand u went back in branch00,\nso u have this following schema:\n\n\n                                    +-- branch00   \n                       +------------+---------------------------+\n                       |                                        |\n\n                       +--------+     +--------+       +--------+       \n               +------>|        +---->|        +------>|        |       \n               |       +--------+     +--------+       +--------+       \n               |\n          +----+---+     +--------+              \n          |        +---->|        |              \n          +--------+     +--------+              \n\n          |                       |\n          +------+----------------+\n                 +-- branch_master\n\nwe can see that branch00 is further than branch_master\n	we can do 2things:	\n		merge\n		rebase\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 15:56:53'),(495,'#git -file_get_back_to_commit00 -checkout',NULL,NULL,'\ngit checkout 3467xshg file00\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 16:30:48'),(496,'#git -get_back_all_repo_to_commit00 -checkout',NULL,NULL,'\ngit checkout r34xds5\n	::::warning:::: remember that u_re in a ghost_branch\n	check that with this\n		git branch\n	u _must_ go back in branch_master\n		git checkout master\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 16:30:48'),(497,'#git -create-branch-after-going-back-in_commit00 -checkout',NULL,NULL,'\nu_re in b_master\nu want to go back in r357xce446 and create a branch automatically\n	git checkout r357xc -b testing\nimmediately u_ve this next:\n\n            +-----+         +------+        +-------+\n            |     +-------->|      +------->|       |\n            +--+--+         +------+        +-------+\n               |             +------+\n               +-------------+      |\n                             +------+\n\n               |                    |\n               +----+---------------+\n                    +- this is done just after the prev cmd\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 16:40:19'),(498,'#git *log -serie01',NULL,NULL,'\ngit log file00\n	to get all _commits_ which modified file00\n\ngit log --since=\"2 days ago\"\n	very explicit\n	OR\n	git log --since=2.days\n\ngit log file00 --since=\"2 days ago\"\n	explicit\n\ngit log --since=\"2 years 1 day 3 minutes ago\"\n	explicit\n\ngit log -n 4 -p\n	to get some info about the 4last commits\n	-p is done to get the modification in each file\n	is the same as:\n		git log -p -n 4\n\ngit log --stat\n	to get the sumUp of the information about the commit\n\ngit log --pretty=oneline\n	this the out\n		ca82a6dff817ec66f44342007202690a93763949 changed the version number\n		085bb3bcb608e1e8451d4b2432f8ecbe6306e7e7 removed unnecessary test code\n		a11bef06a3f659402fe7563abf99ad00de2209e6 first commit\n\ngit log --pretty=format:\"%h — %an, %ar : %s\"\n	out:\n		ca82a6d — Scott Chacon, 11 months ago : changed the version number\n		085bb3b — Scott Chacon, 11 months ago : removed unnecessary test code\n\ngit log --pretty=format:\"%h %s\" --graph\n	out:\n		* 2d3acf9 ignore errors from SIGCHLD on trap\n		*\n		5e3ee11 Merge branch \'master\' of git://github.com/dustin/grit\n		|\n		| * 420eac9 Added a method for getting the current branch.\n		* | 30e367c timeout code and tests\n		* | 5a09431 add timeout protection to grit\n		* | e1193f8 support for heads with slashes in them\n		|/\n		* d6016bc require time for xmlschema\n		*\n		11d191e Merge branch \'defunkt\' into local\n\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 17:35:51'),(499,'#git -long-list *log +--pretty=format:XXXXXXX',NULL,NULL,'\nex:\n	git log --pretty=format:\"%h %s\" --graph\n	\nOption Description du formatage\n%H Somme de contrôle du commit\n%h Somme de contrôle abrégée du commit\n%T Somme de contrôle de l\'arborescence\n%t Somme de contrôle abrégée de l\'arborescence\n%P Sommes de contrôle des parents\n%p Sommes de contrôle abrégées des parents\n%an Nom de l\'auteur\n%ae e-mail de l\'auteur\n%ad Date de l\'auteur (au format de l\'option -date=)\n%ar Date relative de l\'auteur\n%cn Nom du validateur\n%ce e-mail du validateur\n%cd Date du validateur\n%cr Date relative du validateur\n%s Sujet\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 17:35:51'),(500,'#git -long-list *log --XXXXXXX',NULL,NULL,'\nOption Description\n-p Affiche le patch appliqué par chaque commit\n--stat Affiche les statistiques de chaque fichier pour chaque commit\n--shortstat N\'affiche que les ligne modifiées/insérées/effacées de l\'option --stat\n--name-only Affiche la liste des fichiers modifiés après les informations du commit\n--name-status Affiche la liste des fichiers affectés accompagnés des informations d\'ajout/\nmodification/suppression\n--abbrev-commit N\'affiche que les premiers caractères de la somme de contrôle SHA-1\n--relative-date Affiche la date en format relatif (par exemple \"2 weeks ago\" : il y a deux semaines) au lieu du\n--graph Affiche en caractère ASCII le graphe de branches et fusions en vis-à-\nvis de l\'historique\n--pretty=<format>Affiche les commits dans un format alternatif. Les formats incluent oneline, short, full\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 17:35:51'),(501,'#git -long-list *log -XXXX',NULL,NULL,'\nex:	git log --since=2.weeks\n\nOption Description\n-(n) N\'affiche que les n derniers commits\n--since, --after Limite l\'affichage aux commits réalisés après la date spécifiée\n--until, --before Limite l\'affichage aux commits réalisés avant la date spécifiée\n--author Ne montre que les commits dont le champ auteur correspond à la chaîne passée en argument\n--committer Ne montre que les commits dont le champ validateur correspond à la chaîne passée en argument\n\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-02 17:35:51'),(502,'#network -cable# #rj45 -color','\ndroit\n	tx+     orange/white-tracer\n	tx-     orange\n	rx+     green-white_tracer\n	        blue\n	        blue-white_tracer\n	rx-     green\n	        brown-white_tracer\n	        brown\n\ncrossed:\n	orange/white-tracer		             green-white_tracer\n	orange                               green              \n	green-white_tracer                   orange-white_tracer\n	blue                                 brown-white_tracer\n	blue-white_tracer                    brown\n	green                                orange\n	brown-white_tracer                   blue\n	brown                                blue-white_tracer\n	\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-02-03 04:31:03'),(503,'#network -topology_intro','\n3types ppl:\n	bus\n            +----+    +------+\n            | pc |    |  pc  |\n            +--+-+    +--+---+\n               |         |\n          -----+---+--+--+--------     \n                   |  |\n              +----+  +-----+\n              | pc |  | pc  |\n              +----+  +-----+\n\n\n	anneau\n             \n                        +------+\n                        |  pc  |\n          +---+         +----+-+\n          | pc+<--+          |\n          +---+   v  *******<-  \n                   **       **      +---+\n      +----+      *           * <-->+p c|\n      | pc +<---->*           *     +---+\n      +----+      *           * \n                   **       **   +-----+\n        +---+<-----> ******* <-->+ pc  |\n        |p c|        ^           +-----+\n        +---+        |\n                  +--+-+\n                  | pc |\n                  +----+\n\n\n	etoile\n            \n                                +--+                +--+\n                                |PC|<--+       +--->|PC|\n                                +--+   |       |    +--+\n                                       v       v\n                     +--+            +-+-------+---+        +--+\n                     |PC|<---------->+ S W I T C H +<------>|PC|\n                     +--+            +--+---+---+--+        +--+\n                                  